)attr default(%+_)
  _ type( input) intens(low ) just(left ) hilite(uscore) caps(on)
  ~ type(text) intens(high) caps(off) just(asis ) hilite(reverse) color(turq)
  [ type(output) intens(high) caps(off) just(left) pas(on) skip(on) color(white)
)Body Expand(\\)
%Tutorial -\-\~The z ISPF Git Interface (zigi)%\-\- Tutorial
%Selection ===>_ZCMD                                                          +
+
                              %Respository Table
+
%Row Selections:
+
  %A+Add the dataset/file for Commit
+    - Inform git that this dataset/file is to be updated or added to the repo
  %B+Browse the dataset/file
+    - Use ISPF Browse on the z/OS dataset or file%*+
  %RM+Remove the dataset/file from the repository and from git management
+     - Deletes both z/OS datasets and OMVS files
  %RN+Rename the dataset/file
+     - Renames the dataset or file and informs git of the rename
  %S+Edit the dataset/file
+    - Use ISPF Edit on the z/OS dataset or file%*+
  %V+View the local repository files in OMVS
+    - Use ISPF View on the z/OS dataset or file%*+
%*+  If the selection is a directory then convert%B%S%V+to work with it
+
+Press the%Enter+key to continue your zigi tutorial journey.
)Init
 .cursor  = &zcmd
 &zcont = zigih210
)PROC
)END
